They made us buy another hookah after we paid for one because  it was 2 people per Hookah limit. Hands down the best hookah lounge/club in Springfield/West Springfield area. Breath-taking interior design, attentive service, attention to detail, delicious food and a very fun vibe. Would highly recommend to anyone looking for an upscale vibe and experience.

The food was pretty good, the hookah however was trash. Not to mention I went on a Sunday at 830pm and everyone got charged a $10 cover fee. There was only two other people inside with the whole place empty. Won’t be traveling back for this.
Too crowded, they over seat people way to too close to each other, will ask you to share your table with strangers. Good food and drinks but overpriced for the area.

Saturday Night in December. 8:30pm. Was the only customer and was seated in their non VIP. VERY Uncomfortable benches with no back support. So many pillows you have to move them around. You won’t like this place if your used to South FL or LA Hookah lounges. The hostess/waitress was rude to me when I only ordered mint tea. Left a tip with my tea. Would not bring a date here or come back

I also really enjoy their white sauce as well, especially with garlic mixed in, so much each taste and flavor. Their crusts are also worth mentioning because they are always done above and beyond.I also prefer supporting locally owned businesses compared to world-wide chains like Dominos & Papa Johns pizza.

Hookah experience and night life is a great time. It’s small and space is limited so first come first served. There’s a cover charge even before you do anything which I found odd. We got there around 8pm for dinner. They seated us in a great space if we were just doing hookah but it was not feasible for dinner. It was incredibly hard to eat dinner with the tables being small and very close to the floor. Many of us had to put the plates in our laps. Which took away from the experience. We ate as little as possible just to quickly get it packed and out of the way. I’d recommend this place only for hookah not dinner.

I went yesterday for the first time. We weren't greeted. We didn't know that if you sit you must order immediately hookah, liquor...we get the menu and the host is talking to us like we were supposed to know this, making us feel uncomfortable and stupid! Then we start dancing and she comes over and says we can't dance next to the table making fun of us. Then the party next to us (all males) start dancing and she never told them to stop, she would visit them often so obviously they are regulars and they get a special treatment. We also noticed they have favorite customers and treat them differently. My friends drink was spilled on the table once they place the hookah, they charged her for it. We still made the best of it and hopefully we get a different host and we have a Better experience.

Today my girls and I decided to come to le souk. It was a very dissapointing experience. We’ve been there a few other times but today just ruined it for this place. The spot is very ghetto with horrible customer service. We payed a entrance fee of 10 dollars, which was reasonable. The hostess sat us four in a booth, as we were checking the menus she came over and rrushed us with the menus asking us if we were done. Then five minutes later she comes over and tells us to get up and move so other customers can sit in our spot. We ask her if we can stay and they sit in that spot they are trying to make us sit in. We didn’t want to be in the middle. We wanted to sit in the corner so we didn’t have to be close to other random people. The girl says no and tells us to move again and says you guys will be close in the middle too. I found that to be very disrespectful, like how are you going to come and make me get up so other people can sit there when they can sit in the spot that they were trying to make us sit in. We decide to leave and We ask for our money back for the entrance fee. They refuse to give it back. They give us horrible customer service and thats okay, but they can’t give our money back? The employees were completely trying to ignore us, the manager didn’t even come over to see what was going on. The manager was trying to avoid us as well. Someone needs to teach them customer service and how to run a business. I do not recommend anyone to go there. You will be very dissapointed. And just want to say they don’t even deserve that 1 star I just gave them.
Love it !

Chef Kay and her amazing staff hosted an amazing 40th anniversary party for my dear parents. The entire party planning process was seamless. Chef Kay allowed me to drop off the decorations for the party the night before, when I arrived for the party everything was set up.  We had appetizers passed throughout the party. My guest were able to pay for their drinks individually and there was no confusion. The food was hot and fresh.  Chef Kay and staff kept up with keeping my guest fed and comfortable.  Many of my guest would love to use her space to host their next event. Thank you chef Kay, I couldn’t have done this without you.
What an awesome place to come sit smoke some hooka and enjoy food.

Although the environment indeed contained a beautiful atmosphere, I am utterly disgusted with the poor level of customer service and how much of a RIP OFF this place actually is. According to Springfield Massachusetts Law, it is still LEGAL for an 18 year old to be a patron at a hookah lounge, just because they serve alcohol does not prohibit someone from going there just to smoke hookah. That is the same thing as saying you can't sit at a restaurant because they serve wine! The skinny manager does not know proper etiquette or how to show class with patrons, very appalled at such poor management led by her, she did not seemed to be concerned with how her customers felt or have the slightest idea of how to handle a conflict. What is most shocking is how every time you come here there is always a "hidden fee" or cover charge, HOWEVER such fee is considered unethical and illegal, as a business needs to prominently post that, such as a sign, that it levies a cover charge and also list the amount. What is most appalling is how this establishment OVERCHARGES on receipts and exploits from unaware customers. There have been several times that I have been here as a patron, they have charged me for more than one hookah. But the worst experience of all came from the black bouncer in the front. Never have I ever have been that disrespected by a human being. For some reason he always picked on me and does not know how to mind his own business. Did not let me in with my family on their wedding day but let's skimpy little girls go in freely without checking ids and have caught him several times getting paid in cash to let people in. How revolting. This place is by far utterly disgusting in terms of managing their establishment, and I will pursue further legal action for the damages they have caused to me and my friends and family. There are so many other hookah bars out there who won't give you such a hectic experience, but indeed know how to provide a lovely experience for you and your friends and family. They are losing more and more valuable customers who used to come religiously every week from different states. Shame on you guys, you are an embarrassment. This is not Le Souk, this is LE TRASH.

I visited Le Souk hookah lounge during a visit to Boston a with a few  friends. We walked in after a group of people who were welcomed warmly who walked towards a table that was already seated and having drinks. The hostess after being told by my friend that we were a group of 8, before welcoming, smiling and without a beat said to my friend if you are not ordering drinks and only one hookah there is a 1.5 hour limit. Don't plan to stay for 6 hours. She then asked if we still wanted to stay or if we where going to be ordering. i am appalled and believe the reception. I totally understand a busy Saturday night and wanting to get in more revenue but that is not definitely not how a business should build a client base. Service was unacceptably slow- over 30 min for drinks and never checked back on. Music really loud, even above what it would be at a club. Belly dancer however was impressive with sword.

Place looks like dynamite, amazing decor, food was great, guess it's only their first week open so I can understand the wait time and little issues here and there. The belly dancer was rocking the floor. My friends and I had fun.
